value.value: The proportion or number of cells in the male reproductive glands where sperm production occurs.
The volume of or amount of air contained in the lungs at various points of the respiratory cycle.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the movement of gases into and out of the lung.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the organ that secretes pancreatic juice into the duodenum and secretes glucagon and insulin into the bloodstream.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the reduction in the caliber of the bronchus or bronchi.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the mechanism that removes mucus and other foreign particles and microorganisms from the lungs by directed ciliary and secretory activity of the respiratory submucosal glands.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to an involuntary response to a peripheral stimulus.
The point at which one may first detect auditory signals at given frequencies.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the actions or reactions of an organism in response to a tactile stimulus.
The point at which stimulation first elicits the perception of pain.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the organs involved in smell.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the series of events required for an organism to receive an olfactory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal; olfaction involves the detection of chemical composition of an organism's ambient medium by chemoreceptors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to a function of or process in the organs involved in the perception of taste.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability to perceive a particular flavor or suggestion of something imparting a flavor by the chemoreceptors of the gustatory system.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the sharpness or clarity of vision.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of one of the two folded, sac shaped glands that is a diverticulum of the ductus deferens.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to actions or reactions of an organism associated with the ability to receive, store, process or recall informational stimuli.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to actions or reactions of an organism in response to a sensory stimulus; a sensory stimulus is any change in the external environment that is perceived and processed by any of the faculties by which outside stimuli are perceived.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the behavior of animals towards offspring.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to actions or reactions of an organism with regard to the consumption of solids or liquids.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the visual or tactile surface characteristics of the fine, keratinized filamentous growths arising from the epidermis of mammals.
Any measurable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the tubular invaginations of the epidermis from which the hair shaft develops.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process in the embryo that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces to which cells respond and are eventually instructed to differentiate.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of any cell type or tissue in the embryo.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the membranes involved with embryonic protection and nutrition.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes involved with the ability to see.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the organ of vision and its supporting structures.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the deposition or aggregation of coloring matter in the membranous protective covering of the body.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the membranous protective covering of the body.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the stiff hairs projecting from the face, which act as touch receptors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the bone-like structures embedded in the jaw and used for mastication.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the organ of hearing, responsible for maintaining equilibrium as well as sensing sound and divided in mammals into the external ear, the middle ear, and the inner ear.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes involved in the perception of sound.
Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement of an organ or part of the body.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement of an organ or part of the body.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the projecting, paired, jointed appendages of the body used for locomotion or grasping.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the fingers or toes, or their corresponding parts in other vertebrates.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the appendage at the caudal end of the vertebral column in some vertebrates including remnant structures in species that normally lack a tail.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the craniofacial, vertebral, rib, or sternal bones.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the bony framework of the limb, autopod, tail, or fin.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the bones of the face and/or cranium.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the internal equilibrium of lipids (molecules composed of carbon and hydrogen and characteristically insoluble in water) within an organism or cell.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the processes that cause many of the chemical changes in living organisms, including anabolism and catabolism; metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

Any measurable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the development of blood cells; in the fetus, they develop in the aorta, genital ridge and mesonephros region and in adults, in the bone marrow and lymphatic tissues.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the heart or blood vessels.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the system responsible for the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide with the environment.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the system responsible for the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide with the environment.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the paired organs responsible for urine excretion and regulation of ion concentrations.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the paired organs responsible for urine excretion and regulation of ion concentrations.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of any of the tissues of the liver, gall bladder, or bile ducts.
